data.name: label51.Text
data.value: Following thing needs operator to confirm: At last, tool will automatically return to STEP 2, please press button "Robot Current Position" again. The positions that showed by "Before Transplantaion" and "After Transplantation" should be same.

data.name: label25.Text
data.value:
When you press button , tool will check following things to confirm G-HWDEF transplantation has been successfully completed.
1. After rebooting controller in Step 8, controller is running without error. 2. The G-HWDEF information read from motor encoder are same with your input in previous STEP. 3. The firmware package which is unzipped in Step 2 will be deleted.

data.name: label20.Text
data.value: This step will finish following operation: 1. Based on template HWDEF and RBCONST.DEF which in firmware package, creat Generic HWDEF. 2. Transfer Generic HWDEF to controller. 3. The controller will automatically reboot when the transfer is successful.

data.name: label15.Text
data.value:
This step will transfer "sc5000.bin" and "5KSTDRV.bin" to controller, and update system firmware.Select robot type and put these files to path which is same with tool.
When transfer and update are successful: 1. Reboot controller by manual. 2. When the status changes from OFFLINE to , controller will again.

data.name: label27.Text
data.value:
Before press button : 1. User should specify the latest version firmware package. (Use from STEP 3.)
After pressing button "I'm ready to start!": 1. Controller will be backed up. The backup file will be saved in folder "BACKUP". 2. Tool checks if some of the necessary files exist.

data.name: label2.Text
data.value: Please press the button , this position will be shown in "Before Transplantation".When all steps are finished, press the button again. The position will be shown in "After Transplantation." If they are same, means G-HWDEF transplantation is succeed. If not, please execute "SetZero".
